text: Elkridge is an unincorporated community and census-designated place (CDP) in Howard County, Maryland, United States. The population was 25,171 at the 2020 census. It was founded early in the 18th century. Elkridge is located at the three counties, the other two being Anne Arundel and Baltimore counties. ==References== Category:Unincorporated communities in Maryland Category:Census-designated places in Maryland
